Re: Otaku?
by Hyperworm » Wed 09.24.2008 5:09 pm Doesn't it simply depend on the person? Some people acknowledge that they're otaku and take some element of pride in it regardless of how the wider community might see them. Within circles of people like that, otaku will be a positive term (a term for people who share the same interests as the group).On the other hand other people might not like to be associated with that image and will take offense. ._.
fun translation snippets | need something translated?BTC@1KMZXgoWiDshQis5Z7feCx8jaiP4QAB2ks
